abstraction :(handling the accessibility)

polymorphism :polymorphism means ability to take more than one form. An operation may exhibit different behaviors in different instances. FUNCTION OVERLOADING AND OPERATOR OVERLOADING
Polymorphism is extensively used in implementing inheritance

encapsulation : data and function 

Inheritance: inheritance is the process by which objects of one class acquire the properties of objects of another class

Interfaces : enforcing the classes to implement certain functionalities.

cohesion : how related responsibilities are together
coupling : how modules are dependent on each other